node.text: On this episode of DMTV Milkshake, we talk to Melodie Leung, associate director with @zahahadidarchitects. node.text: For this week’s Milkshake, we spoke to @bimmawilliams, co-founder and host of the @claimastories podcast. Claima — ”claima” as in “claim a seat at the table” — is a podcast with a mission: to give young BIPOC creatives the inspiration, and roadmap, they need to make good on their ambitions. Bimma joins us from the road — specifically from, a custom-rigged 1993 Mitsubishi Delica Starwagon rechristened as “Storytella,” his mobile podcast studio during a 30-day, four-city tour of the West Coast. Here, he gives his best advice for young BIPOC creatives looking for professional advancement and shares a few of the stories that have moved him most. \\\ #dmtvmilkshake #designmilktv

🔄 Rotate Your Device 🔄
Inside the Dallas studio of sculptor Dan Lam (@sopopomo), burbling, bubbling and bright works of art appear to move on their own. Commissioned by @Genesis_usa, the artist transformed her distinct style into her first-ever digital art car and NFT inspired by her time in the G70. Lam took inspiration from her time driving the G70, and worked with digital designer Stephen Judge (@stephenthejudge) to bring her vision of the world passing outside the windows to life. #G70artcars #GenesisG70 #G70 #artcars #digitalartcars #NFTs #BorntoMove

node.title: Sculptor Dan Lam Blends the Outside World into Her Genesis G70 Art Car

DMTV Milkshake: Mastering the Art of ‘Interior Marketing’ \\\

node.text: eBikes are cropping up everywhere, and with the advances in technology making the electric bicycle more affordable (and therefore more ubiquitous) it's only natural that manufacturers would begin exploring new aesthetic options. @officialcrowncruiser Motors founder Adebola Adeleye wants to satiate your need for speed with an electric bike that embodies the spirit of British heritage motorcycles. The CrownCruiser's carbon fiber frame is wrapped in classic motorcycle detailing and outfitted with a set of components inspired by F1 racecars. And if the “dark and menacing aesthetic” isn’t quite your cup of tea, keep your eyes peeled for more variations coming soon. \\\ Read more about the CrownCruiser at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: Friday is finally here! 🎉 For today's Friday Five, we're joined by Barbados native Jennifer Graham. Jennifer is an Associate Principal at @perkinswill, as well as Vice President of Action at @iidanychapter and, as a champion for DEI (Diversity, Equality and Inclusion), social purpose and sustainability, Jennifer brings these issues front and center in her client work and community service. The influence of Jennifer’s family and the values they share are evident in everything she does – from fulfilling her father’s own dream of working in architecture to ravenously pursuing knowledge (a trait passed down from her own grandmother). \\\ Check out a sampling of Jennifer's work here, then head to the link in bio to read more about Jennifer and find her five picks for today's Friday's Five. 🔗

node.text: The Wave Collection holds Uchronia Casa’s first furniture designs that are being introduced during Paris Design Week. As the name of Uchronia Casa's new furniture collection might suggest, the Wave Collection explores the undulations of water through various scales and forms – from a large table to the detailed filigree of chair struts. Every piece of furniture seems to be a fresh take on French savoir-faire, challenging and graphic. Throughout the collection you’ll come across stucco-marble, raku and resin finishes that contribute to the feeling. When viewed together, it's clear how each design expounds up the last, almost like a ripple making its way through each form. \\\ Read more about the Wave Collection at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: With fall emerging, Scandinavian design and feelings of hygge come to mind. And as we transition to a quieter, more tranquil time of year, so too does our monthly mood. To set the tone for our focus on natural tranquility, we bring you @villakuro. Situated in the remote desert landscape of Joshua Tree, California the Villa Kuro vacation home seems to have been transplanted from Japan. This desert abode was designed by Elaine Chao and Stanley Yang of @miniinno and inspired by nature and the Japanese philosophy of wabi-sabi which seeks to find beauty in imperfection. Filled with natural textures, warm and minimal interiors, and contemporary furnishings, Villa Kuro is the picture-perfect escape away from the city. \\\ Read more about Villa Kuro at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: Another design force looking to make an impact, @mon.terra was founded by Tamara Efrat, a multidisciplinary designer and entrepreneur, and Yuval Dishon, a process engineer and maker. node.text: As artists and makers continue to consider their individual roles in the environmental crisis, the young designers participating in @ukurant_’s Perspectives exhibition take a hard look at their work's impact. They’ll challenge your notions of material and shape, innovative composites and known techniques to create a fresh view of sculptural and narrative value. \\\ Learn more about the Perspectives exhibition at the link in bio. 🔗
